BMI Health Calculator

User can input their height (in either meters + cm or feet + inches) and weight (kg or lb)

User taps “Calculate” and sees their BMI displayed (with one decimal place)

User sees which category their BMI falls into (e.g., < 18.5 underweight; 18.5-24.9 healthy; 25-29.9 overweight; ≥ 30 obese) 
Healthline
+3
Cleveland Clinic
+3
Saint Luke's Health System
+3

User can copy the BMI value and category to clipboard/share (for example via a “Share result” button)

Bonus features

User can toggle between metric (kg + m) and imperial (lb + in) units

User can view a history of past BMI calculations (with date/time)

User can add height/weight entries for tracking over time and see a simple chart of BMI trend


Useful links and resources:
